In .NET 10, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer works because Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30+) and .NET 10 MAUI embraces edge-to-edge/window insets instead.

**Recommended approach — react to keyboard (IME) insets on Android:**

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Ensure edge-to-edge and listen for keyboard insets
        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav bar bottom inset
            int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottomPadding);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**For your XAML layout**, structure it so the input bar is at the bottom of a `Grid`:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

**On iOS**, the soft input adjustment still works by default — MAUI auto-scrolls for focused entries. If needed, you can add `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect()` / `Connect()` to customize behavior, but typically iOS "just works."

**Key points:**
- The IME insets listener pushes content up by exactly the keyboard height
- It also handles the case when the keyboard dismisses (insets go to 0)
- This replaces the old `AdjustResize` behavior with the modern Android insets API
